abstract:
In this paper, we deal with the following mixed local/nonlocal
Schr\"{o}dinger equation
  \begin{equation*}
  \left\{
  \begin{array}{ll}
  - \Delta u + (-\Delta)^s u+u = u^p \quad \hbox{in $\mathbb{R}^n$,}
  u>0 \quad \hbox{in $\mathbb{R}^n$,}
  \lim\limits_{|x|\to+\infty}u(x)=0,
  \end{array}
  \right.
  \end{equation*} where $n\geqslant2$, $s\in (0,1)$ and
$p\in\left(1,\frac{n+2}{n-2}\right)$.
  The existence of positive solutions for the above problem is proved, relying
on some new regularity results. In addition, we study the power-type decay and
the radial symmetry properties of such solutions.
  The methods make use also of some basic properties of the heat kernel and the
Bessel kernel associated with the operator $- \Delta + (-\Delta)^s$: in this
context, we provide self-contained proofs of these results based on Fourier
analysis techniques.
